	<tr><td>c</td><td>d</td></tr>
</tbody></table></th><th></th></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></tabl=
e>
<p>The determinant of <b><i>A</i></b> using the Leibniz formula is:</p>
<table align=3D"center"><tbody><tr><td>|A| =3D </td><td><table class=3D"mat=
rixTable">
	<tbody><tr><td>a</td><td>b</td></tr>
	<tr><td>c</td><td>d</td></tr>
</tbody></table></td><td> =3D ad - bc</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>Note that taking the determinant is typically indicated with "| |" surro=
unding the given matrix. Given:</p>
